span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ubraskdembones.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Brask Dembones</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>h0x0r!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(10/18/01 10:03:02 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> HoT on Calendar???</span><hr size=1> I haven't payed real close attention to this, but is HoT considered a valid entry on the Lany's calendar?  Are people attempting to honor these entries?<br>
<br>
Only reason I ask this is because last night I was scheduled to go into ToV with a guild that had scheduled it and been planning for a week.  36 people were expecting to get in there and I, probably along with many others, took the extra effort to get all the way out there the night before to make sure we were ready.  As soon as I logged on last night I was informed that it was cancelled....that another guild had already moved into HoT.<br>
<br>
Now please let me emphasize here...I'm not laying blame on anyone, to my knowledge we haven't really developed a policy regarding this place other than that it's FFA.  It would have been nice to receive some prior warning so we could plan something else /shrug but no big deal.  It DOES however require similar planning and effort as PoH and PoF though and for that I feel bad for the raid leader that put the effort in, should HoT be treated the same on calendar?<br>
<br>
Before anyone jumps on me for whining, let me just add that FFA is fine with me.  I'm pretty confident that I could put together 2 strong groups and go in there with very little notice.  My main concern is for guilds like mine that are just getting enough peeps in the +55 category that they can attempt this with the proper time to plan it out.  Should we at least attempt to honor the calendar for this?<br>
<br>
Brask Dembones<br>
Warlord of 60 Seasons<br>
Bears of Oboo <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#D5D4D5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uleolan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Leolan</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_bluespot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle><FONT COLOR=AA0000><B>Lanys.com Administrator</B></FONT></span><br> <font color=#000033>(10/18/01 10:21:29 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: HoT on Calendar???</span><hr size=1> It's been said a lot before.  HoT is a big place.  After talking to some people who were there, it sounded like your raid leader simply didn't bother to try to move in deeper.  It'll be a long time before there are no mobs to kill in HoT. <p> - Leo<br>
