<br>
But you did answer my question, HoT will probably always be FFA.  Now I know <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#D5D4D5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uulaian.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ulaian</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>I live here.... get out.</span><br> <font color=#000033>(10/18/01 11:43:21 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: HoT on Calendar???</span><hr size=1> I've been on a raid or two where we literally ran out of mobs to pull <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  Although of course these were a bit bigger than 2-3 groups. For the most part HoT can support 2 groups, and maybe even 3 groups killing, depending on the size of the individual raids.<br>
<br>
But if you end up with 6 groups of high level people, like i've seen it happen, you can clear it all by yourself hehe. <p>Ulaian Moonleaf <BR>
-Warder <BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#E5E5E6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uazzigothghul.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Azzigoth Ghul</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>I live here.... get out.</span><br> <font color=#000033>(10/18/01 12:24:47 pm)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: HoT on Calendar???</span><hr size=1>      The biggest concern with PoF and PoH is that the mobs respawn on a longer timer 11-14hrs.  That is why posting intent to raid is important for planning.  It's no fun showing up to an empty plane.  Or having to sit and wait for mobs to pop.<br>
<br>
HoT mobs respawn in 1hr 15min.<br>
<br>
     It can support 2 raids, but 1 must enter the halls which is more difficult.  The raid on the platform faces little risk other than a bad pull, or someone sitting to close to pit.  It's also a faster CR if they wipe out.<br>
     The hall raid must face roamers, and being pulled over by the other raid.  The CR can be longer.<br>
     It's not possible to share the platform since the casters use the wall to block AE, and the mobs would just add to each other.<br>
<br>
     If your goal is to mass farm armor, then you want low risk, and lots of kills.  The platform is the ideal spot.<br>
<br>
     In the past if 2 raids wanted the HoT platform, they typically randomed for it.  Also merging raids might be an option for 2 smaller raids.  Halls are not that bad if you march in with a strong experienced crew.<br>
<br>
Azzi <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#D5D4D5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ugusiamroa.showPublicProfile?language=EN>GusiamROA</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>l33t d00d!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(10/18/01 12:31:33 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: HoT on Calendar???</span><hr size=1> Hot isnt as hard as planning a pof or poh raid. Since It can be done with 1 group.  1 good group can take out 2 aoe mobs with little probs.  I know, I have done it before.  <br>
<br>
I believe raids like poh and pof should be schedled.  I have lead those raids and know how much work is involved in those.  Hot on the other hand you just slap 1 to 4 groups together and your good to go.  Your best bet is when you want to do HoT.  Let other dragon aligned guilds know that you plan on doing it a certain time. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ugusiamroa.showPublicProfile?language=EN>GusiamROA</A> at: 10/18/01 12:35:31 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#E5E5E6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ubraskdembones.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Brask Dembones</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>h0x0r!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(10/18/01 12:53:04 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: HoT on Calendar???</span><hr size=1> /nod That's kinds of what I was getting at.  Is it better to use a centralized tool like the calendar for this communication? or go to each website and drop a post?  This raid last night was on the calendar so I'm guessing a more informal approach needs to be used in the future to avoid conflict.<br>
<br>
As for PoH/PoF taking more planning....yeah I'd agree with that in general, but only because lower levels are involved.  I'm sure you could whip together that 1 to 4 groups that you were going to take to HoT and they would fair just as well in either of those other planes....not that you would ever need to do that though.  But then again I'm not a raid leader, so I should prolley shut my trap hehe.<br>
<br>
Thanks for the input guys. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#D5D4D5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uzxing.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zxing</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>h0x0r!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(10/18/01 10:46:49 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: HoT on Calendar???</span><hr size=1> Gusiam, what you said makes very little sense in comparing it to poh/pof when you consider that come classes can solo in pof, and 1 well equiped group that could do hot, can also do pof/poh with very little problems.<br>
<br>
Some guilds aren't well equiped, and can't do things like HoT with one group yet. Guess what it boils down to is, next time you guys go...since you've done oh so great things there is, have the balls to move into the halls and let the less equiped people have the platform.<br>
<br>
