<br>Warlord of Fallen Legacy
<br>Lanys T`Vyl</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#E5E5E6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ualundraadjani.showPublicProfile?language=EN>AlundraAdjani</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.theroyalknights.org/sigs/btnappcurley1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>I live here.... get out.</span><br> <font color=#000033>(10/19/01 4:56:57 am)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.theroyalknights.org/sigs/appquistis.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: HoT on Calendar???</span><hr size=1> I don't feel safe going deep into the halls if there is only one raid in HoT, but I do if there are two...why?  Because the other raid can always CR us if things get messy.  I think an ideal solution to this would be that if a second raid comes in and wants to do HoT, they move deeper in and the &quot;platform&quot; raid agrees to CR them if they are wiped out.<br>
<br>
I also don't see any problem with posting it on the calendar to let other guilds know your intention.  Perhaps you should specify that you would like to hold a *platform* HoT raid and that anyone else is welcome to come and move deeper in...since a spur of the moment raid is far more likely to be equipped and experienced enough to do so. <p><center><img src="http://www.theroyalknights.org/sigs/adjsig7.gif" >
