<br>
I guess all I'm looking for is some &quot;general rule&quot; to follow for this in the future.  If the Oboo decide to hold their first HoT raid in the next month or so would you recommend me dropping a post on your web page just to give a heads up?  Is a calendar posting enough? or are they basically SOL if someone feels like going in ahead of them?<br>
<br>
Brask <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#D5D4D5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/utanisemanasponge.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tanise Manasponge</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>p0\/\/3r-p0sT3r!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(10/19/01 5:45:43 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: HoT on Calendar???</span><hr size=1> Personally I see np with listing in on the calendar. It's funny but all the people here who preach that the calendar is simply an information tool seem to forget that when it comes to Hot. <br>
<br>
All you are doing is informing peeps that you will be there. <br>
<br>
I could easily post on my guilds boards a planned hot raid then all trek over that at the set time only to find out that there's currently a raid in hot because Guild b did the same as me posted on their own boards. <br>
<br>
How else other then the calendar are you supposed to know if someones planning to be there? Visit every other Hot capable guild's boards and check their raid listings?<br>
<br>
In Addition to that Hot can support at least 2 raids. 1 Ent 1 exit. As soon as I get back from my happy little trip to Chicago I'm planning to host an exit raid.<br>
<br>
Also you need the calendar if you plan to hold an open raid so people have the ability to sign up now granted with hot it'ss not as big an issue but for other things it is. Now that Zland isn't a big deal with Visions I want to hold an open Zland raid and I plan to use the calendar to see exactly how many people are interested. Plan to with Vind as well. Granted for those I may just stick with the raid board for sign up rather then posting it on the calendar but why is it such a big deal if it goes on the calendar?<br>
<br>
I think I was the first person to throw hot on the calendar. And I copped shit over it. I planned a raid for the same day as MW. It was no biggy Azz just bumped his raid and even if he hadn't I woulda bumped mine or we would have joined together. Had I not put it on the calendar MW woulda shown up to find my raid already in progress (i think I was set for 1 hr before theirs) and they woulda had a whole bunch of people in a currently raided zone. Granted Azz and I woulda worked something out quite easily but my putting it on the calendar actually made things able to be dealt with ahead of time rather then talking in tells while I was trying to continue my raid to keep ahead of the respawn. What about if they showed up and then decided to move their raid...What about the peeps that had actually planned around this raid? Peeps do do that. I know I have. I've taken days off work for certain raids. Sure would piss me off to find out the day of that it was cancelled.<br>
<br>
Peeps go fucking gonzo at Visions for clearing fear w/o putting it on the calendar and mucking up a sched. raid yet if a Hot raid is planned on and they show up and there's already a guild raiding there it's no biggie? How is it different? Because Hot spawn is only 72 minutes? Oh yeah I see lots of raids only stay for 1 spawn. Hot raids normally last as long as a planar raid chances are good that if you have a raid planned for the same time another guild does yours will be cancelled. Yeah you can go in as soon as Guild A gets done and have stuff to kill (something that needs to be fixed planeswise) but you prolly will not have as long a raid as you planned to because by the time guild A is done and you get start peeps need to log sleep etc.<br>
<br>
Maybe my insomnia has faulted up my thinking but I just don't see any prob with it and only see it being beneficial.<br>
<br>
